<subSubSection pageId="32" pageNumber="33" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="32.[533,1536,346,856]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[565,669,589,613]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Remarks:</emphasis>
The BIN, BOLD:AAC2064 includes DNA barcodes recorded as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Blyth" authorityYear="1844" box="[1353,1469,589,613]" class="Mammalia" family="Rhinolophidae" genus="Rhinolophus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="macrotis">
<emphasis box="[1353,1369,590,613]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">R</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1380,1469,590,613]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">macrotis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gyldenstolpe" authorityYear="1917" box="[533,659,624,648]" class="Mammalia" family="Rhinolophidae" genus="Rhinolophus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="siamensis">
<emphasis box="[533,549,624,647]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">R</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[561,659,624,647]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">siamensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and both demonstrated very shallow genetic divergences [
<bibRefCitation author="Francis CM &amp; Borisenko AV &amp; Ivanova NV &amp; Eger JL &amp; Lim BK &amp; Guillen-Servent A" box="[1286,1299,624,648]" journalOrPublisher="PloS one." pageId="32" pageNumber="33" pagination="12575" part="5" refId="ref37870" refString="4. Francis CM, Borisenko AV, Ivanova NV, Eger JL, Lim BK, Guillen-Servent A, et al. The role of DNA barcodes in understanding and conservation of mammal diversity in Southeast Asia. PloS one. 2010 Sep 3. 5 (9): e 12575. https: // doi. org / 10.1371 / journal. pone. 0012575 PMID: 20838635" title="The role of DNA barcodes in understanding and conservation of mammal diversity in Southeast Asia" type="journal article" year="2010">4</bibRefCitation>
] (S5 Fig). The BIN, BOLD:ACU9422 contains two DNA barcodes which are originally from GenBank and may be erroneous.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="32.[533,1536,346,856]" box="[565,870,728,752]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[565,710,728,752]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">IUCN status:</emphasis>
Least Concern
</paragraph>
